{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|grc|κεραμικός||potter's}}, from {{m|grc|κέραμος||potter's clay}}, perhaps from a pre-Hellenic word.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|GenAm|RP}} {{IPA|/səˈɹæmɪk/|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|æmɪk|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Made of material produced by the high-temperature firing of inorganic, nonmetallic rocks and minerals.
#: {{ux|en|A '''ceramic''' vase stood on the table.}}

